<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-il-PYhN0UG9ED_VFc-HbUg" name=",_NteloKZ9EeCmPtYkD7g0pw" guid="-il-PYhN0UG9ED_VFc-HbUg" changeDate="2011-08-24T06:47:01.787-0700" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Only after each stage of the safety lifecycle has been completed and evidence for compliance given at the functional&#xD;
    safety assessment can the release for production report be prepared.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The release for production of the item can only be approved if the functional safety assessment report and safety&#xD;
    case&amp;nbsp;are satisfactory and provide confidence of functional safety.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    The documentation for the release of production must include the following information.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        The name and signature of the person in charge of the release.&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        The version/s of the released item.&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        The configuration of the released item, these should be baselines for hardware and software and be under&#xD;
        configuration management.&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        References to associated documents.&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        The release date.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Known safety anomalies shall be solved.&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote></mainDescription>
  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Approves the item for production and operation.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
